    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> There's however a bug when returning to the first page:\r\n\r\nNice catch!\r\nI only thought about receiving previous page by \"show previous\" button.\r\nI should fix it somehow.\r\n\r\n> In a more generic way, the pagination doesn't work as expected now. If you select page 3, you've got 60 results. If you come back to page 2, you still get 60 results.\r\n\r\nYeah, this is a weird behavior when we use infiniteHits + pagination.\r\nI guess, it would be also weird if we get rid of the last 20 results when coming back to page 2. (we could scroll, though)",
